00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,610
Come on. All right, all
right, that's enough.

236
00:16:52,612 --> 00:16:56,013
- Are you okay? Honey?
- Enough. Enough.

237
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,883
I just wanted Christmas to be like
it used to be, but forget it.

238
00:16:58,885 --> 00:17:01,452
I hate Christmas!
I hate all of you!

239
00:17:01,454 --> 00:17:04,054
Max. Max!

240
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:06,457
Oh, lay off of him.

241
00:17:06,459 --> 00:17:08,692
Kid deserves a prize
just for telling the truth.

242
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:22,306
- Can I come in?
- - No.

243
00:17:22,308 --> 00:17:26,143
You know, they're leaving
right after Christmas,

244
00:17:26,145 --> 00:17:29,580
so we only have to survive
another... three days.

245
00:17:29,582 --> 00:17:31,215
I don't get it.

246
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:33,150
Every year it gets worse.

247
00:17:33,152 --> 00:17:35,886
Why do we have to put up with their
crap just because we share DNA?

248
00:17:38,423 --> 00:17:42,126
Because that's what
a family is, Max.

249
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:43,994
People you try
to be friends with

250
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:46,497
even though you don't have
a whole lot in common.

251
00:17:46,499 --> 00:17:49,266
But why? Because.

252
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:50,734
Well...

253
00:17:52,471 --> 00:17:54,972
Okay, you kind of got me there.

254
00:17:57,243 --> 00:18:01,912
Or maybe it makes us work a little harder to
find what we do have in common, you know.

255
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:05,449
Put everything aside, think
of other people for a change.

256
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:08,185
Friends, family,

257
00:18:08,187 --> 00:18:10,754
even the assholes
you normally can't stand.

258
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:13,691
Like uncle Howard?
Didn't wanna name names.

259
00:18:15,927 --> 00:18:18,562
Dad, do you really
believe in all that?

260
00:18:19,664 --> 00:18:21,599
I want to, Max.

261
00:18:24,469 --> 00:18:26,770
But, hey,

262
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:29,773
bet there's still time to drop
that letter in the mailbox, huh?

263
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:29,126
Don't you find it
the least bit strange?

264
00:20:29,128 --> 00:20:30,928
They can see
dust specks on Mars,

265
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:33,731
but no one noticed a giant
blizzard hurtling towards us.

266
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:35,633
Well, as soon
as the power's back,

267
00:20:35,635 --> 00:20:38,636
you can write an angry e-mail
to the national weather service.

268
00:20:38,638 --> 00:20:41,005
But in the meantime,
let's just try and stay calm.

269
00:20:41,007 --> 00:20:43,841
Mom, there's something weird outside.
I am calm.

270
00:20:43,843 --> 00:20:46,810
I would just be calmer if I knew how
we were gonna survive Christmas

271
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:50,681
with 12 people stuck in a house with no
hot water, no heat and no electricity.

272
00:20:50,683 --> 00:20:55,085
Or food. Well, there's
plenty of leftovers, Howard.

273
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:58,122
- Beer it is.
- Phone's dead too.

274
00:20:58,124 --> 00:21:00,157
- Mom!
- What, Max?

275
00:21:00,159 --> 00:21:01,558
There's a snowman in our yard.

276
00:21:03,294 --> 00:21:04,762
See?

277
00:21:07,298 --> 00:21:10,000
That's... That's great, Max.

278
00:21:10,002 --> 00:21:12,002
But who built it?

279
00:21:12,004 --> 00:21:16,140
You can barely see across the street,
but it doesn't look like it's just us.

280
00:21:16,142 --> 00:21:19,777
I can walk over, check with the turners.
The turners are in Hawaii.

281
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:22,479
The Lamberts are in Florida, and the
Cartwrights stopped talking to us

282
00:21:22,481 --> 00:21:26,150
after Max's noodle incident.
After his what?

283
00:21:26,152 --> 00:21:29,987
Max, please go and get Omi out of the fireplace
before she burns the whole house down.

284
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:33,957
I'll get it!

285
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:35,893
Fine.

286
00:21:35,895 --> 00:21:37,428
Seriously, what are we gonna do?

287
00:21:38,396 --> 00:21:39,897
Ooh! Merry Christmas.

288
00:21:39,899 --> 00:21:43,467
Sign here. Yeah. Wow.

289
00:21:43,469 --> 00:21:46,570
Honey, stuff to carry!

290
00:21:46,572 --> 00:21:48,305
Some weather, huh? Yeah.

291
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:51,175
It's a ghost town out there.
Roads are a nightmare.

292
00:21:51,177 --> 00:21:53,811
Yeah, no kidding.
Hey, these too?

293
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:55,512
Uh, not mine.

294
00:21:55,514 --> 00:21:57,915
Uh, must be from the boys in brown.
All right.

295
00:21:57,917 --> 00:22:00,651
Merry Christmas. Yeah, you too.

296
00:22:00,653 --> 00:22:03,087
Ah, what is it?
Hey, look at this, huh?

297
00:22:03,089 --> 00:22:06,056
What? They got more stuff.

298
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:08,092
How come rich people
get all the free shit?

299
00:22:08,094 --> 00:22:11,028
I don't know, honey.
Democrats, probably.

300
00:22:13,032 --> 00:22:15,332
Oh, my god!

301
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:18,235
Who needs this much cheese?

302
00:22:18,237 --> 00:22:20,571
One singular moment.

303
00:22:20,573 --> 00:22:23,774
You guys, I've texted Derek, like, nine
times and he still hasn't written back.

304
00:22:23,776 --> 00:22:25,542
That is not normal.

305
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:27,911
It's the blizzard, honey.
Nothing's working right now.

306
00:22:27,913 --> 00:22:31,048
Can I walk over and check on him?
It's only a few blocks.

307
00:22:31,050 --> 00:22:33,717
I don't think
that's a good idea.

308
00:22:33,719 --> 00:22:36,964
I could see if anyone
else has power on the way.

309
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:38,288
She'll be fine.

310
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:40,591
Okay. One hour.

311
00:22:40,593 --> 00:22:43,627
When you get back, I want you to spend
some girl time with Jordan and Stevie.

312
00:22:43,629 --> 00:22:45,195
Got it?

313
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:47,131
You call that a reversal?

314
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:49,233
Come on, Jordy, plant your feet!

315
00:22:49,235 --> 00:22:51,435
Plant your feet. All right.
Right.

316
00:22:51,437 --> 00:22:54,404
You know what I mean. Thanks.

317
00:22:54,406 --> 00:22:57,207
Be careful, okay?
Okay. Back later.

318
00:22:57,209 --> 00:22:59,710
Love you. One hour.

319
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:01,378
Okay.

320
00:23:03,882 --> 00:23:06,283
Max, I told you
to get Omi out of the...

321
00:23:18,463 --> 00:23:20,330
She says hot chocolate
makes everything better.

322
00:24:41,379 --> 00:24:43,680
Oh, my god.

323
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:52,322
Please!

324
00:24:57,396 --> 00:24:59,863
Somebody help me!

325
00:24:59,865 --> 00:25:01,765
Please!

326
00:25:01,767 --> 00:25:03,333
Daddy!

327
00:25:07,673 --> 00:25:09,306
Help!

328
00:27:28,212 --> 00:27:29,646
Get anything?

329
00:27:30,715 --> 00:27:32,082
No.

330
00:27:34,185 --> 00:27:38,488
It's the weirdest thing. There's no
cars, no people, not even a salt truck.

331
00:27:40,491 --> 00:27:43,493
Don't suppose you got me a backup
generator for Christmas, did you?

332
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:47,931
Yeah, it's under the tree next
to your ties and underwear.

333
00:27:47,933 --> 00:27:49,399
Good.

334
00:27:54,539 --> 00:27:57,274
It's getting late.

335
00:27:57,276 --> 00:28:00,177
Beth should be home by now. She's fine.
She's at Derek's.

336
00:28:00,179 --> 00:28:02,179
All the more reason to worry.

337
00:28:02,181 --> 00:28:05,949
Hey, hon, relax.
Just for once, okay?

338
00:28:09,587 --> 00:28:12,255
How's everybody else doing?

339
00:28:12,257 --> 00:28:17,894
You know, cranky, bored,
sick of the snow.

340
00:28:17,896 --> 00:28:20,097
And each other. 'Tis the season.

341
00:28:25,369 --> 00:28:27,104
Oh, god, I miss us.

342
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:31,141
Me too.

343
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:41,852
Mom, dad.

344
00:28:43,488 --> 00:28:45,622
It's already dark out
and Beth isn't back yet.

345
00:28:52,163 --> 00:28:54,064
Hey, Howard.

346
00:28:54,066 --> 00:28:57,067
Do you think your Hummer could
get through this mess? Lucinda?

347
00:28:57,069 --> 00:29:00,070
I could point her due east,
hit the gas

348
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:02,806
and she'd be storming the
beaches at Normandy by sunrise.

349
00:29:02,808 --> 00:29:05,408
What's on your mind, t?
Well, it's-it's Beth.

350
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:08,245
She went to her boyfriend's earlier
and she hasn't come back yet.

351
00:29:08,247 --> 00:29:13,116
See? Let them out of your sight for one
second, and boom, shotgun wedding.

352
00:29:13,118 --> 00:29:15,352
Aunt Dorothy, please.

353
00:29:15,354 --> 00:29:17,187
Well, you ought to know.

354
00:29:17,189 --> 00:29:21,024
It's probably nothing. But I
thought we'd go pick her up,

355
00:29:21,026 --> 00:29:23,994
take a quick swing around town,
see what's going on out there.

356
00:29:23,996 --> 00:29:26,930
A little recon mission, huh?
Thought you'd never ask.

357
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,798
- Okay.
- Go to mama.

358
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,867
Yep. All righty.

359
00:29:30,869 --> 00:29:33,370
Thomas. Thomas.

360
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:37,474
What? Why?

361
00:29:37,476 --> 00:29:39,342
What the hell is she
so riled up about?

362
00:29:43,681 --> 00:29:45,549
She says not to go.

363
00:29:45,551 --> 00:29:48,051
That it's too dangerous, and that we
should wait until the storm's over.

364
00:29:48,053 --> 00:29:49,686
- Tom.
- No, I got this.

365
00:29:49,688 --> 00:29:52,122
Hey, mom, we have
to go pick up Beth,

366
00:29:52,124 --> 00:29:54,824
but Max and Sarah will take care
of you while I'm gone, okay?

367
00:29:54,826 --> 00:29:57,160
Mom. Hey, mom, listen.

368
00:30:00,732 --> 00:30:02,699
Everything's gonna be okay.

369
00:30:24,989 --> 00:30:27,724
Global warming, my ass.

370
00:30:27,726 --> 00:30:30,694
Must be negative 20 out here.

371
00:30:30,696 --> 00:30:32,996
This just doesn't
make any sense.

372
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,332
You try am?
Yeah, I tried everything.

373
00:30:35,334 --> 00:30:38,301
The storm probably knocked
out the radio stations too.

374
00:30:39,370 --> 00:30:41,171
I guess so.

375
00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:45,008
What I wouldn't give for a little
bing Crosby right about now.

376
00:30:52,049 --> 00:30:53,583
All right, slow down.

377
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:55,285
What is that?

378
00:31:05,429 --> 00:31:06,963
Is that a snowplow?

379
00:31:10,434 --> 00:31:12,869
Ahh.

380
00:31:16,574 --> 00:31:18,508
Hello?

381
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:44,434
Christ.

382
00:31:44,436 --> 00:31:47,437
Poor bastard must have
sailed clear through.

383
00:31:47,439 --> 00:31:50,473
Looks more like the opposite.

384
00:31:50,475 --> 00:31:52,075
What do you mean?

385
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:54,844
The glass is punched in.

386
00:32:08,159 --> 00:32:10,327
We got to find Beth.

387
00:32:13,364 --> 00:32:17,000
You packed guns on Christmas.

388
00:32:17,002 --> 00:32:19,369
Always be prepared, boy scout.

389
00:32:20,671 --> 00:32:22,339
It's kind of heavy.

390
00:32:22,341 --> 00:32:26,076
Yeah. It's Linda's.

391
00:32:37,655 --> 00:32:39,422
Oh, my gosh.

392
00:32:40,558 --> 00:32:43,059
You had mom's angel
this whole time?

393
00:32:43,061 --> 00:32:44,961
Yeah. I thought you knew.

394
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:46,463
No.

395
00:32:48,566 --> 00:32:50,200
Oh.

396
00:32:50,202 --> 00:32:52,869
Remember we used to fight
over who got to place her?

397
00:32:52,871 --> 00:32:57,140
Yeah. You fought dirty.
I still have the scars.

398
00:32:57,142 --> 00:32:59,642
Where do you think
my girls get it from?

399
00:33:04,348 --> 00:33:07,117
Wow. You saved everything.

400
00:33:08,185 --> 00:33:10,186
Yeah.

401
00:33:10,188 --> 00:33:12,489
I figured that's what mom
would have done, you know.

402
00:33:24,369 --> 00:33:26,336
Mom?

403
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,940
Probably just squirrels.

404
00:33:30,942 --> 00:33:33,343
In this weather?

405
00:34:02,106 --> 00:34:04,073
See?

406
00:34:04,075 --> 00:34:05,708
- Squirrels.
- Right.

407
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:08,611
Probably playing
with their nuts.

408
00:34:26,163 --> 00:34:27,630
Beth?

409
00:34:34,739 --> 00:34:36,473
Derek!

410
00:34:39,009 --> 00:34:40,343
Beth!

411
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:43,179
Quiet, Tommy. I don't like this.

412
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:09,372
Whoever did this is
a demented son of a bitch.

413
00:35:18,682 --> 00:35:21,251
Don't worry. We'll
find her, buddy.

414
00:35:32,062 --> 00:35:34,063
Looks like a gas line blew.

415
00:35:44,074 --> 00:35:45,909
What's that?

416
00:35:50,247 --> 00:35:52,649
I've hunted a lot of game
in my day.

417
00:35:52,651 --> 00:35:56,152
Those are hooves. Big ones too.

418
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:59,155
Could be an elk or a goat.

419
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:02,258
What kind of goat
walks on its hind legs?

420
00:36:08,165 --> 00:36:09,165
Beth!

421
00:36:11,235 --> 00:36:13,069
Beth!

422
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:16,072
Beth!

423
00:36:20,010 --> 00:36:21,411
Beth!

424
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:24,948
Beth!

425
00:36:26,784 --> 00:36:29,052
- Beth!
- Tommy!

426
00:36:29,054 --> 00:36:31,588
Wait up!

427
00:36:41,432 --> 00:36:42,699
Howard!

428
00:36:48,639 --> 00:36:52,041
- Oh, my god!
- Hold on, Howard!

429
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:54,210
Help! Oh, god! Help me!

430
00:36:56,281 --> 00:36:57,814
Come on! Tommy!

431
00:36:57,816 --> 00:36:59,048
Aah!

432
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:01,985
Something...
Something's biting me!

433
00:37:01,987 --> 00:37:04,087
Don't let go!

434
00:37:10,327 --> 00:37:12,195
Tommy?

435
00:37:21,639 --> 00:37:23,906
Let's go!

436
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:25,575
What was that thing?

437
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:27,243
I don't know,
but we have to move!

438
00:37:35,419 --> 00:37:37,820
Oh, my god. Oh.

439
00:37:40,624 --> 00:37:43,326
Lucinda!

440
00:37:45,129 --> 00:37:47,797
Where do you think you're going?

441
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:49,799
To find them. I don't like this.

442
00:37:49,801 --> 00:37:52,835
What are you talking about? Tom and Howard
know what they're doing. They're fine.

443
00:37:52,837 --> 00:37:55,204
- Are they?
- Mom?

444
00:37:55,206 --> 00:37:58,474
Honey, I'll be right back. I promise.
Just lock the door...

445
00:37:58,476 --> 00:38:02,345
Oh, god! Max, get the first aid kit!
Sarah, lock the door!

446
00:38:02,347 --> 00:38:04,614
Girls! Make some room
for your dad!

447
00:38:04,616 --> 00:38:06,182
- Get the door!
- Shut the door!

448
00:38:06,184 --> 00:38:08,484
Where's Beth? We heard gunshots!

449
00:38:08,486 --> 00:38:12,388
I'll explain everything, but right now everybody
just needs to stay calm and stay inside!

450
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:14,724
And get away from the windows!

451
00:38:14,726 --> 00:38:16,959
Swords, guns, knives, pots, pans!
Get whatever you can...

452
00:38:16,961 --> 00:38:18,361
Howard! What?

453
00:38:18,363 --> 00:38:20,363
Not here.

454
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:23,066
Jiminy Christmas.

455
00:38:23,068 --> 00:38:26,202
What happened out there?
Nothing.

456
00:38:26,204 --> 00:38:28,738
It's just a scratch.

457
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:31,507
- Oh, my god. It looks like something bit you.
- Nope.

458
00:38:31,509 --> 00:38:33,710
Probably a bear trap
under the snow or something.

459
00:38:33,712 --> 00:38:35,044
We don't have bears here.

460
00:38:38,215 --> 00:38:40,516
Okay. Um...

461
00:38:40,518 --> 00:38:43,486
Kids, why don't you go into the kitchen
and get something to eat now, okay?

462
00:38:43,488 --> 00:38:45,421
You just don't wanna tell us
what's going on here!

463
00:38:45,423 --> 00:38:47,523
Everybody into the kitchen
right now, Max, okay? Right now.

464
00:38:47,525 --> 00:38:49,892
Come on. Let's go.
Girls, come on.

465
00:38:49,894 --> 00:38:52,921
Aunt Dorothy, will you
keep an eye on them?

466
00:38:52,947 --> 00:38:53,930
Why me?

467
00:38:53,932 --> 00:38:56,299
I never liked kids,
even when I<i> was</i> one.

468
00:38:58,569 --> 00:38:59,769
Please.

469
00:38:59,771 --> 00:39:02,071
Oh, all right.

470
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:04,440
All right!

471
00:39:04,442 --> 00:39:07,677
Come on, guys. I'm gonna teach you
how to make peppermint schnapps.

472
00:39:11,582 --> 00:39:12,782
Mom.

473
00:39:12,784 --> 00:39:15,184
Mom, will you please go
into the kitchen

474
00:39:15,186 --> 00:39:17,420
and help with the kids?

475
00:39:26,063 --> 00:39:28,197
Come here, baby.

476
00:39:30,267 --> 00:39:34,270
See? A little sugar
and a little spice...

477
00:39:34,272 --> 00:39:36,606
Uh-huh...

478
00:39:36,608 --> 00:39:39,542
Makes everything nice.

479
00:39:41,478 --> 00:39:43,346
Mmm.

480
00:39:48,953 --> 00:39:52,054
All right.
But don't you rat me out.

481
00:39:54,424 --> 00:39:57,760
Who or what did all this?

482
00:39:57,762 --> 00:40:01,764
Your guess is as good as mine.

483
00:40:01,766 --> 00:40:04,433
First I thought
it was a gang thing.

484
00:40:04,435 --> 00:40:07,503
But between this and all the
crazy stuff we saw out here,

485
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:09,105
it just doesn't add up.

486
00:40:09,107 --> 00:40:11,407
It could be terrorists, right?

487
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:14,977
Yeah, terrorists. Maybe traded their
suicide vests for rabid snow dogs?

488
00:40:14,979 --> 00:40:16,679
Tommy!

489
00:40:16,681 --> 00:40:18,281
Tom, god! Sorry. Sorry.

490
00:40:18,283 --> 00:40:20,483
And, um...

491
00:40:21,652 --> 00:40:23,686
- Beth?
- Okay.

492
