Mom, what are you talking about?

602
00:50:26,190 --> 00:50:28,056
Please, listen.

603
00:50:28,058 --> 00:50:30,492
English. I knew it.

604
00:50:31,461 --> 00:50:33,295
I must tell you something.

605
00:50:33,297 --> 00:50:35,264
To all of you.

606
00:50:37,901 --> 00:50:41,403
It started with the wind.

607
00:50:45,309 --> 00:50:49,044
<i>On a cold winter night,
much like this.</i>

608
00:50:50,547 --> 00:50:52,815
<i>It was almost Christmas.</i>

609
00:50:54,217 --> 00:50:57,719
<i>But this Christmas was darker,</i>

610
00:50:57,721 --> 00:50:59,321
<i>less cheerful.</i>

611
00:51:01,958 --> 00:51:04,960
<i>But I still believed in Santa,</i>

612
00:51:06,296 --> 00:51:08,464
<i>in magic,</i>

613
00:51:08,466 --> 00:51:11,400
<i>and miracles</i>

614
00:51:11,402 --> 00:51:15,838
<i>and the hope
that we could find joy again.</i>

615
00:51:17,507 --> 00:51:20,275
<i>But our village had given up</i>

616
00:51:20,277 --> 00:51:22,911
<i>on miracles and on each other.</i>

617
00:51:26,749 --> 00:51:30,085
<i>They had forgotten
the spirit of Christmas,</i>

618
00:51:30,087 --> 00:51:32,421
<i>the sacrifice of giving.</i>

619
00:51:35,091 --> 00:51:38,560
<i>And my family was no different.</i>

620
00:51:42,365 --> 00:51:46,034
<i>I tried to help them
to believe again,</i>

621
00:51:46,036 --> 00:51:50,405
<i>but we were no longer
the loving family I remembered.</i>

622
00:51:53,943 --> 00:51:56,578
<i>They too had given up.</i>

623
00:51:58,214 --> 00:52:01,550
<i>And eventually, so did I.</i>

624
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:07,122
<i>And for the first time,</i>

625
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:09,525
<i>I didn't wish for a miracle.</i>

626
00:52:10,460 --> 00:52:13,529
<i>I wished for them to go away.</i>

627
00:52:14,998 --> 00:52:18,433
<i>A wish I would come to regret.</i>

628
00:52:21,138 --> 00:52:23,238
<i>And that night,</i>

629
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:26,909
<i>in the darkness
of a howling blizzard,</i>

630
00:52:26,911 --> 00:52:29,444
<i>I got my wish.</i>

631
00:52:33,517 --> 00:52:38,687
<i>I knew Saint Nicholas
was not coming this year.</i>

632
00:52:41,391 --> 00:52:44,660
<i>Instead it was a much darker,</i>

633
00:52:44,662 --> 00:52:47,563
<i>more ancient spirit.</i>

634
00:52:50,833 --> 00:52:54,236
<i>The shadow of Saint Nicholas.</i>

635
00:52:54,238 --> 00:52:56,638
<i>It was Krampus.</i>

636
00:52:59,075 --> 00:53:03,245
<i>And as he had
for thousands of years,</i>

637
00:53:03,247 --> 00:53:08,216
<i>Krampus came not to reward,
but to punish.</i>

638
00:53:08,218 --> 00:53:11,820
<i>Not to give, but to take.</i>

639
00:53:13,189 --> 00:53:15,757
<i>He and his helpers.</i>

640
00:53:18,729 --> 00:53:20,929
<i>I could only listen</i>

641
00:53:20,931 --> 00:53:24,700
<i>as they dragged my family
into the underworld,</i>

642
00:53:24,702 --> 00:53:28,637
<i>knowing that I would be next.</i>

643
00:53:30,307 --> 00:53:34,476
<i>But Krampus
didn't take me that night.</i>

644
00:53:36,145 --> 00:53:38,947
<i>He left me as a reminder</i>

645
00:53:38,949 --> 00:53:43,251
<i>of what happens
when hope is lost,</i>

646
00:53:43,253 --> 00:53:46,622
<i>when belief is forgotten</i>

647
00:53:46,624 --> 00:53:50,392
<i>and the Christmas spirit dies.</i>

648
00:54:05,908 --> 00:54:08,143
And here I thought
I was the one losing it.

649
00:54:08,145 --> 00:54:10,445
Howard. What?

650
00:54:10,447 --> 00:54:13,281
You believe this senile horseshit?
